    <h3>Producer Company</h3>
    <p style="padding-left: 22px;">A Producer Company in India is governed by the Companies Act 2013 that is legally recognised body 
        of farmers and agriculturists. The Companies Act defines Producer as any person engaged in any activity connected with or relatable
         to any primary produce. A Producer Company is thus a body corporate having an object that is one or all of the following:</p>
<p style="padding-left: 22px;"> harvesting, procurement, grading, pooling, handling, marketing, selling, export
     of primary produce of the Members or import of goods or services for their benefit.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 22px;">A Producer Company can be formed by either of the following –</p>
    <p>i. 10 or more producers, or</p>
    <p>ii.	2 or more producer institutions, or</p>  
 <p>iii.	A combination of 10 or more producers and producer institutions</p>               
 </div>    


